# Introdution to c++

C++ is an object-oriented programming language, which means it allows you to define classes and objects to model real words entities and their behavior.

## Name convections
### Private atributte in a class


## Object Oriented programming in C++
Object oriented programming aims to implemente real-world entities like inheritance, hiding, polymorphism, etc in programming 

These are some basic concepts  that act as the building blocks of OPPs:
-	Class
-	Object
-	Encapsulation
-	Abstraction
-	Polymorphism
-	Inheritance
-	Dynamic binding
-	Message passing

### Class
A class ia user-defined data type that has data members ans members functions.
